      <div>
        <p>Josh Sellers is a graphic designer, photographer, nonprofit strategist, and systems thinker based in Kings Mountain, NC. As a biracial, gay, Christian creative, Josh works at the seam where creativity, strategy, and advocacy meet. He leads branding campaigns, crafts grants, and builds justice‑centered programs across churches, arts groups, and community organizations—honoring legacy while building what’s next.</p>
        <p>Through JaiSellers Designs and JaiSellers Consulting, Josh centers equity and cultural preservation, blending brand storytelling with concrete tools like fiscal sponsorship, 1023s, 990s, OKRs, and grant strategy. He’s developing <em>The People’s Brand Guide</em> to help leaders communicate clearly and lead with purpose.</p>
